snippet.textDisplay: Well, moving a player to a more physical and high intensity league will always carry a fair bit of uncertainty. Will he adjust? Can he keep his performance levels? But I personally think there are several encouraging facts about Bruno. He’s been captain and has shown he can carry a team in big games, his mentality seems stronger than Sancho, Maddison and Grealish in my opinion. Grealish doesnt seem like a great team captain in tough games. The papers say he took a pay cut when the team was in financial trouble, if that’s true, i would have a lot of respect for him. Paper says he wanted to move to a better team (his stats deserve it), his boss got greedy and he did not get his transfer in the summer. Normally what would happen? The player throws a tantrum, look at Pogba and Eriksen. Not this guy, he kept his stats up in the past 6 months. That’s professionalism to me. I would take a 60m chance on him rather than a 100m gamble on a wild teenager like Sancho definitely. Maddison at 100m+ is also crazy, people would expect him to perform like Messi at that money, the pressure could crush him

snippet.textDisplay:
) Following a three-day public hearing in December 2018, the second public hearing of the Independent People's Tribunal/China Tribunal was held in London on April 6-7, 2019.

Twenty-three witnesses attended the tribunal, including researchers, medical professionals, journalists, and survivors of the atrocities committed by the Chinese communist regime from around the world. They gave testimonies before the tribunal regarding allegations of state-sanctioned organ harvesting targeting persecuted groups in China. Chaired by Sir Geoffrey Nice, QC, the panel consisted of seven experts tasked with conducting the world’s first-ever independent analysis of forced organ extraction in China.
